A probe is underway into circumstances around the release from custody of two members of Shepherd Bushiri's legal team. The pair appeared briefly in the Pretoria Magistrate's Court on Monday. etv's Pule Letshwiti-Jones has more. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANESBURG - A probe into circumstances around the release from custody of two members of Shepherd Bushiri's legal team is underway. Terrance Baloyi and Alvin Khosa appeared briefly in the Pretoria Magistrate's Court on Monday but the matter could not be enrolled. READ: Shepherd Bushiri accused of rape The pair were detained for eight hours allegedly for falsifying statements. Bushiri and his wife, Mary, are facing fraud and corruption charges in South Africa. They fled the country for Malawi shortly after receiving bail.